snippet.textDisplay:
TL:DR on the WSB/Gamestop situation: Big brokers and elites have promised to buy more than all of the supply of the Gamestop stock, betting on the likelihood that there will be very little demand. WSB realized this and started buying and buying the stock, "artificially" creating significant demand. Now the elites, who promised to buy these stocks expecting them to be very cheap, will have to buy vastly more expensive shares and will lose A LOT of money. And they are mad because they got caught being risky with lots of money, and they stand to lose billions and billions for it.


It's important to understand that WSB started buying Gamestop shares en masse because big broker/investing companies had been "shorting" the stock for several months. Shorting a stock is basically when you promise to buy a share, sell the promised share for money now, and then, when it comes time for you to buy the share for real, you've gambled that the stock will be lower in value, netting you a profit. The risk is that if the stock gains value in that time period, you will lose that difference. And because the stock can gain a LOT more value than you might have promised to buy if for, you could lose a significant amount of money. That is the risk of shorting a stock. These companies have actually been doing it to Gamestop (and other companies like AMC) particularly harshly, forcing their stock from $20ish each to $3ish per share over 2020. The biggest kicker is that they've shorted GME %140; they have promised to buy %140 of the shares that exist, banking on the fact that Gamestop is doing poorly and they will therefore turn a profit when they actually have to buy the shares.  Also shorting a stock over %100 is kinda illegal and definitely scummy, because you're trying to devalue a company on purpose.

At some point last summer-ish, some of the lovelies over at r/wallstreetbets noticed that GME was the most shorted stock in the country, and decided to start buying shares. This means that the value of the shares started to go up. This went relatively slowly until a few days ago as WSB realized that if they kept buying these stocks, then the value would increase. Indefinitely. These brokers and investors, who have promised to buy %140 of the stock that exists, will be forced to pay TREMENDOUS amounts of money when the bill comes due. So, partially to turn a handsome profit but mostly to spite the elites, WSB started buying as much of GME as they could, and the price began skyrocketing. This has made the brokers and co. very upset, as they already stand to lose billions and billions of dollars for this, and that loss is increasing literally by the minute. They were playing a very risky, scummy game and they got called out for it, and they will suffer tremendously because of it.

Many of them and the people they probably pay have taken to the news and media and probably brigaded r/WSB (partially why it's private rn), saying all sorts of things to dissuade redditors and their sympathizers from costing them more and more and more money. They have been largely unsuccessful, as reddit intends to see this to the sweet sweet end, where the brokers will lose billions and they will profit, both in money and in elitist tears. ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€ðŸš€
